    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - ADJUSTMENTS - HEADLAMP REPLACEMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="4">
        <title>HEADLAMP REPLACEMENT</title>
        <para>To replace head lamp and directional bulbs, unlatch hood on both sides and tilt hood forward.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the rear side of the headlight housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the socket cover and remove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900852">Figure 52, Item 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove light socket pigtail plug (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900853">Figure 53, Item 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900852" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900852.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 52. Head Lamp Replacement</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY MOUNTING STUD WITH NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SOCKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0900853" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900853.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 53. Bulb Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEAD LAMP PLUG</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. PLUG HOUSING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Twist bulb retainer and lift up.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove seal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900854">Figure 54, Item 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove halogen bulb (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900855">Figure 55, Item 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900854" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900854.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 54. Seal Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT ADJUSTMENT SCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT HARNESS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SOCKET SEAL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0900855" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900855.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 55. Bulb Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT HALOGEN BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ADJUSTMENT SCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT HARNESS</callout1>
                <callout1>5. HEADLIGHT PLUG</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
